lure is usually catastrophic once fracture is initiated. The accent of materials development programs is thus on increasing tensile strength to inhibit fracture initiation. For refractory materials, which are much weaker, catastrophic failure is rarer; the emphasis is on improving the fracture toughness to minimize the amount of cracking.},
